This paper deals with the computation of Nash equilibria in bimatrix games, which is a central topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also presents a linear time algorithm, which suggests that it may be related to computational complexity and algorithms, hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of strategic equivalence, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and machine learning, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The paper also deals with the rank of matrices, which is a topic in linear algebra, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the convergence of algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, hence cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category.
